name: Caladium.1
description:
Second piece of the series "Venenosa" of brazilian native&poisonous plants. 

Native in South America and Brazil, this Caladium is known for it wonderful, colorful and arrow-shaped leaves(sometimes it's kind heart-shaped), presenting a huge variation os patterns.
It have calcium oxalate, which turns this joyfull plant into a very toxic one (not only when it's eaten, but also when it comes in contact with mucous membranes - beware if you have kids or pets, you might keep the Caladium out of reach).

ID: Caladium bicolor

I'm a brazilian woman artist, you can find me at twitter by @ocvvvlta.
